+The spike brief says "append in `addMessage()` (single insertion point)". That is **not sufficient** for assistant replies in the default SDK streaming path.
+
+- `addMessage()` is used for user messages and some non-stream/error paths.
+- Streaming assistant replies are created via:
+  - `TWibWobMessageView::startStreamingMessage(...)` at `app/wibwob_view.cpp:132`
+  - `appendToStreamingMessage(...)` at `app/wibwob_view.cpp:160`
+  - `finishStreamingMessage(...)` at `app/wibwob_view.cpp:174`
+
+If you only hook `addMessage()`, `get_chat_history` may miss streamed assistant responses.
